author: @rtlinfo
title: Osaka tombe au deuxième tour contre Muchova
text: Dans une tenue noire assortie de rubans inspirée d'une tendance japonaise "Lolita gothique", Osaka a servi à 5-4 pour le gain de la deuxième manche, se procurant même deux balles de set, mais a vu la Tchèque revenir et l'emporter au tie-break sur une volée ratée. Quatre fois titrée en Majeur (US Open 2018 et 2020, Open d'Australie 2019 et 2021) et ex-N.1 mondiale, Naomi Osaka avait mis un terme à sa saison en septembre 2022 pour soigner des pépins physiques et sa santé mentale, avant de donner naissance à sa fille Shai en juillet 2023. Revenue sur le circuit en janvier, elle avait déjà été stoppée au deuxième tour de Roland-Garros et de Wimbledon. "Ce qui est difficile, c'est que je ne peux juger mon retour qu'à partir de mes résultats. Je me sens plus rapide, plus forte, mais je perds au 2e tour. C'est dur", a-t-elle concédé. "Je prends ces défaites à coeur. Je ne veux pas sonner trop dramatique, mais mon coeur s'arrête à chaque fois que je perds. C'est pénible, mais j'apprends à être plus mature et à être capable de parler de mes défaites." "J'ai l'impression de travailler plus dur que jamais, ça doit finir par payer. De façon assez ironique, je n'ai toujours pas rejoué de finale, mais mon cerveau est persuadé que je peux gagner ces tournois. Je sens qu'à un moment, les pièces vont s'emboîter. Peut-être pas aussi vite qu'espéré, mais je pense que ça va le faire", a-t-elle ajouté.

author: Nikki Buchanan
title: Dining Review: Thanks a Brunch in Gilbert
text:
Opened: October 2023
This cheery mom-and-pop is a new player in the Gilbert brunch game, offering burritos, Benedicts, hangover bowls of nachos and loaded fries, scrambled egg-filled tacos, avocado toasts, wraps, salads, sandwiches and burgers. The bummer is, almost everything in the breakfast section looks and tastes the same – a pretty jumble of ingredients that are ultimately unexciting. Breakfast bacon fries, built on wimpy waffle fries (why not real fries?), are saggy, ineffective scoops for scrambled egg, bacon, cheese fondue, avocado, salsa, pickled onions and cilantro ($15). And guess what? If you swap waffle fries for corn tortillas, the mix-and-match tacos (one sausage, one bacon, one green chile, $16) are essentially the same thing. I can find far better tacos for less money.
Steak and eggs Benedict (i.e., carne asada and cheese fondue, $15) are too much like the loaded fries, which are too much like the tacos. Blah cheese fondue is no substitute for hollandaise, either. Best savory dish by a mile? A charred, juicy burger topped with feta and red onion jam ($16). This I like.
Wild Card: Florid French toast in various iterations – cookie butter tiramisu, bananas Foster and ridiculously good prickly pear cheesecake on a pretzel crust (crunchy, creamy, sweet and tart all at once, $12). Deliciously fun and worth the drive.
734 N. McQueen Rd., Gilbert,
801-564-2174, thanksabrunchaz.com

author: Presstv
title: Iraq’s terrorism fight would have failed without General Soleimani: Former PM
text: Iraq’s former Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki has praised late Iranian General Qassem Soleimani for the role he played in anti-terrorism fight in the Arab country, saying Iraq would have failed to defeat Daesh terrorists if it was not for Soleimani’s assistance. Maliki made the remarks on Saturday during a ceremony held in the Iranian embassy in Baghdad to remember Gen. Soleimani, a top military commander who was assassinated in a US drone strike on January 3, 2020 when he was leaving Baghdad's airport along with Iraqi paramilitary commander Abu Mahdi al-Muhandis and other comrades. “We could not have fought Daesh if it was not for efforts by Martyr Soleimani and Abu Mahdi al-Muhandis and the Iraqi nation,” said Maliki in the ceremony. Senior Iraqi government officials and politicians attended the memorial service where clerics and notable figures from Iraqi areas liberated from Daesh occupation were also present, according to Iran’s official IRNA news agency. Falih Al-Fayyadh, who leads Popular Mobilization Forces (PMF), a powerful paramilitary group operating within the ranks of the Iraqi army, said in the service that Iran played a major role in Iraq’s fight against Daesh. However, Fayyadh rejected suggestions that Iran has gained a military foothold in Iraq because of the generous support it has offered to the country in recent years. “Some are trying to pretend that that the PMF depends on Iran but this is gibberish talk of the enemy and the weak people,” he said. Daesh controlled swaths of land in Iraq until 2013 when it was expelled from the Arab country by the Iraqi army and popular mobilization fighters. author: CMS Medios
title: Amazon lanzará su primer lote de satélites Kuiper para llevar Internet a todo el mundo
text:
Amazon lanzará su primer lote de satélites Kuiper para llevar Internet a todo el mundo
El lanzamiento de los mismos será transmitido en vivo en la pagina web de la tienda en línea
Amazon anunció que el próximo 9 de abril lanzará el primer lote de satélites de su ambicioso proyecto Kuiper, destinado a proporcionar Internet de alta velocidad a cualquier rincón del planeta.
La misión, denominada KA-01 (Kuiper Atlas 1), despegará desde la Estación Espacial de Cabo Cañaveral en Florida, a bordo de un cohete de United Launch Alliance (ULA). A las 12:00 EST (16:00 GMT), los 27 satélites de este primer envío se desplegarán a 450 kilómetros de altitud, brindando conectividad con baja latencia y alta velocidad.
.[@ProjectKuiper]is set to begin a full-scale deployment of its satellite constellation, with the launch of 27 satellites on a ULA Atlas V rocket. Follow[@ulalaunch]for the latest on launch, and learn more about what to expect from the mission here:[https://t.co/FngVeU8Bm6][pic.twitter.com/JKi3jkcAwu]— Amazon News (@amazonnews)[April 2, 2025]
Te puede interesar: Estos son los dispositivos compatibles con Apple Intelligence en español
El proyecto Kuiper contempla una red de más de tres mil 200 satélites en órbita terrestre baja (menos de dos mil km de altitud). Una vez en el espacio, los satélites serán gestionados desde el centro de operaciones de Amazon en Redmond, Washington.
El vicepresidente del proyecto, Rajeev Badyal, destacó que esta misión es solo el comienzo de la iniciativa, tras múltiples pruebas en tierra. Los nuevos satélites presentan mejoras tecnológicas respecto a los prototipos lanzados en octubre de 2023, optimizando su rendimiento en comunicación, procesamiento y generación de energía.
Con Kuiper, Amazon entrará en competencia directa con Starlink, de Elon Musk, que ya cuenta con más de siete mil satélites operativos, además de rivales como OneWeb y SpaceSail (China).
Lee también: ¿Por qué debes desactivar el WiFi de tu celular al salir de casa?
Amazon ofrecerá una retransmisión en vivo del lanzamiento en su página web, iniciando 20 minutos antes del despegue.
